{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "00e807d9-2413-4b87-b55c-de33cd79f424",
    "name": "Patient Data Manager API",
    "description": "# variables\n\nhave defined variable values for ease of use.\n\nfor the most part, will not require any changes to the request aside from these and the body.\n\n| **variables** | **usage** |\n| --- | --- |\n| apim_env | used to toggle between environments |\n| signed_jwt | used to get the below token |\n| apigee_auth_token | obtained from APIM's identity service |\n| resource_type | resource types available to DHC currently are: Observation or RiskAssessment |\n| resource_id | must be a uuid |\n\n# **how to use**\n\naside from `/ping` all requests to PDM require an access token.\n\n## obtain access token\n\nsign a JWT with private key and api key, and send using `/oauth2/token`\n\ncopy the value of `access_token` into `apigee_auth_token`\n\n## get /{resource}\n\n**CANNOT** be used without params.\n\nuseful for specific filtering options whereby the `resource_id` of a resource isn't known.\n\n`_tag=$PDM_SELF` is used to obtain resources owned by our service, keep this toggled on.\n\n## get /{resource}/{resource_id}\n\nreturns a resource under the specified type and id provided\n\n## put /{resource}/{resource_id}\n\nwill upsert a resource of type and id (create if doesn't exist, update if it does)\n\n**IMPORTANT**\n\nPUT requests will need to carry either an `If-Match` an `If-None-Match` header and all returned resources will carry an `ETag` response header\n\n- resource created or queried, returned with `ETag: 12345` header\n    \n    - to further update resource by ID the request `PUT /{resource}/{resource_id}`\n        \n        - must contain `If-Match: 12345`\n            \n- resource is upserted (does NOT exist already)\n    \n    - must contain `If-None-Match: \\\\*`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.0.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "3570035"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "APIM /{resource}/{resource_id}",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "var uuid = require('uuid');",
              "",
              "var privateKey = pm.environment.get('apim_consumer_private_key') || '';",
              "var envName = pm.environment.get('apim_env_name') || '';",
              "var apiKeyValue = pm.environment.get('apim_api_key') || '';",
              "",
              "if (!privateKey) {",
              "    throw new Error(\"Variable private_key must be set with your private key for signed JWT authentication.\");",
              "}",
              "",
              "if (!apiKeyValue) {",
              "    throw new Error(\"Variable api_key must be set with your integration testing application API key.\");",
              "}",
              "",
              "var auth_url = `https://${envName}.api.service.nhs.uk/oauth2/token`;",
              "",
              "console.log(auth_url);",
              "",
              "var navigator = {};",
              "var window = {};",
              "const interval = setTimeout(() => {}, 2147483647);",
              "",
              "return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {        ",
              "    if (pm.globals.has('jsrsasign-js') && pm.globals.get('jsrsasign-js') !== \"\") {",
              "        return resolve();",
              "    }",
              "",
              "    pm.sendRequest(",
              "        {",
              "            url: 'https://kjur.github.io/jsrsasign/jsrsasign-all-min.js',",
              "            method: 'GET'",
              "        }, function (err, res) {",
              "            if (err) {",
              "                return reject(err);",
              "            }",
              "",
              "            pm.globals.set('jsrsasign-js', res.text());            ",
              "            return resolve();",
              "        }",
              "    );",
              "}).then(() => {             ",
              "    eval(pm.globals.get(\"jsrsasign-js\"));        ",
              "",
              "    // Set headers for JWT",
              "    var header = {",
              "        'typ': 'JWT',",
              "        'alg': 'RS512',",
              "        'kid': 'dev-1'",
              "    };",
              "",
              "    // Prepare timestamp in seconds",
              "    var currentTimestamp = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000)",
              "    var uuid = require('uuid');",
              "    var jti_value = uuid.v4();",
              "    var data = {",
              "        'sub': apiKeyValue,",
              "        'iss': apiKeyValue,",
              "        'jti': jti_value,",
              "        'aud': auth_url,",
              "        'exp': currentTimestamp + 180, // expiry time is 180 seconds from time of creation",
              "    }    ",
              "",
              "    var sJWT = KJUR.jws.JWS.sign(header.alg, JSON.stringify(header), JSON.stringify(data), privateKey);    ",
              "    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {                              ",
              "        pm.sendRequest({",
              "            url: auth_url,",
              "            method: \"POST\",",
              "            header: {",
              "                \"Content-Type\": \"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\"",
              "            },",
              "            body: {",
              "                mode: \"urlencoded\",",
              "                urlencoded: [",
              "                    {",
              "                        key: \"grant_type\",",
              "                        value: \"client_credentials\"",
              "                    },",
              "                    {",
              "                        key: \"client_assertion_type\",",
              "                        value: \"urn:ietf:params:oauth:client-assertion-type:jwt-bearer\",",
              "                    },",
              "                    {",
              "                        key: \"client_assertion\",",
              "                        value: sJWT",
              "                    }",
              "                ]",
              "            }",
              "        }, function (err, res) {                                            ",
              "            if (err) {",
              "                return reject(err);",
              "            }",
              "",
              "            //assign the authorization header value",
              "            pm.environment.set('authorization_header_value', `Bearer ${res.json().access_token}`);",
              "",
              "            //assign the message batch reference",
              "            pm.environment.set(\"message_batch_reference\", uuid.v4());",
              "",
              "            //assign the message reference",
              "            pm.environment.set(\"message_reference\", uuid.v4());",
              "",
              "            //generate a correlation identifier",
              "            pm.environment.set(\"correlation_id\", uuid.v4());",
              "",
              "            return resolve();",
              "        });        ",
              "    });",
              "}).then(() => {    ",
              "    clearTimeout(interval);",
              "}).catch((err) => {     ",
              "    console.error(err); ",
              "    clearTimeout(interval);    ",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
      ],
      "protocolProfileBehavior": {
        "disableBodyPruning": true
      },
      "request": {
        "auth": {
          "type": "noauth"
        },
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Accept",
            "value": "application/json"
          },
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          },
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "{{authorization_header_value}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "key": "X-Request-ID",
            "value": "{{$randomUUID}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "key": "NHSE-Product-ID",
            "value": "{{product_id}}",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "",
          "options": {
            "raw": {
              "language": "json"
            }
          }
        },
        "url": "https://{{apim_env_name}}.api.service.nhs.uk/patient-data-manager/FHIR/R4/Observation/fc335b25-5618-4c12-bef0-df9e139478d8"
      },
      "response": []
    },
